headline: 2 Dividend Stocks to Double Up on Right Now
summary: Walmart (NYSE: WMT) and Home Depot (NYSE: HD) have long histories of raising payouts and should continue providing capital appreciation opportunities.  Walmart has become a household name with its widespread namesake stores and Sam's Club stores.  People continue to see Walmart as a place to shop and spend money.

headline: 2 Magnificent Stocks That I'm "Never" Selling
summary: If you're looking for stocks in the consumer goods space to own and never sell, then you want companies that are clear market leaders that have shown over time that they are adaptable.  When it comes to adaptability in the consumer goods sector, there are two companies that come immediately to mind that have shown the ability to adapt and thrive.  Perhaps no company has shown to been more innovative and adaptable than Amazon (NASDAQ: AMZN) over the past 25 years.
